# Gitignored files a fresh worktree needs that git won't carry over.
# Allowlist (NOT a blanket copy): one path or glob per line, `#` comments allowed.
# Copied into new worktrees by dotagents' WorktreeCreate hook (Claude paths) and,
# for the manual `git worktree add` path, by `npm run worktree:init` — both copy
# (never symlink) from the primary checkout. See package.json `worktree:init`.
#
# Only env files belong here: a symlinked .env.local trips Vite's server.fs.allow, so it must be
# copied. All worktrees share ONE Supabase stack on the default ports (54321/54322/1025), so the
# verbatim copy from the primary checkout is already correct — no per-worktree port-patching.
# Do NOT add node_modules / dist / caches (re-created by `npm ci`) or scripts/data/users.json
# (symlinked by db:link-worktree-data).
.env.local
.env.*.local
